Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and markedly increased total bilirubin, suggesting possible liver dysfunction or biliary obstruction. Other parameters, including liver enzymes and electrolytes, are within normal limits. Further clinical correlation and additional investigations are recommended to clarify the underlying causes.
